    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 11 @ 2021/2022",
    "Question": {
      "content": "If one speaks of measuring an AC voltage of 120V from an electric outlet using an AC voltmeter, it will read about",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "120V",
        "85V",
        "170V",
        "85A"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "120V"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Understanding AC Voltage Measurements</h3><p>When measuring AC voltage:</p><ol><li><strong>RMS vs. Peak Voltage</strong>:<br>AC voltages are typically specified as <strong>RMS (Root Mean Square)</strong> values. For a sinusoidal waveform:<br><p style='background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'>\\( V_{\\text{RMS}} = \\frac{V_{\\text{peak}}}{\\sqrt{2}} \\)</p></li><li><strong>Given Value</strong>:<br>The question states <strong>120V</strong>, which is the standard RMS voltage for household outlets in many countries (e.g., the US).</li><li><strong>Voltmeter Function</strong>:<br>An AC voltmeter is calibrated to display the <strong>RMS voltage</strong>, not the peak voltage. Thus, it will read <strong>120V</strong> directly.</li><li><strong>Peak Voltage Calculation</strong>:<br>For reference, the peak voltage for 120V RMS is:<br><p style='background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'>\\( V_{\\text{peak}} = 120 \\times \\sqrt{2} \\approx 170V \\)</p></li><li><strong>Options Analysis</strong>:<ul><li><strong>120V</strong>: Correct (RMS reading).</li><li><strong>85V</strong>: Incorrect (might confuse with European standards or misapplied calculation).</li><li><strong>170V</strong>: Incorrect (this is the peak voltage, not what the voltmeter reads).</li><li><strong>85A</strong>: Incorrect (units are for current, not voltage).</li></ul></li></ol><p style='color: #27ae60;'><strong>Conclusion</strong>: The voltmeter will read <strong>120V</strong>, the RMS value of the AC voltage.</p></div>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "AC Voltage",
      "Electric Potential",
      "Electric Current",
      "Units of Measurement"
    ]
