    "name": "Question 21 @ 2021/2022",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A generator delivers an AC voltage given by the equation V=120Sin55t. What is the peak voltage of the generator?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "120V",
        "55V",
        "12V",
        "60V"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "120V"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "The AC voltage is given by \\( V = V_0 \\sin(\\omega t) \\). Comparing with \\( V = 120 \\sin(55t) \\), the peak voltage \\( V_0 \\) is 120V. This makes 120V the correct answer. 55V relates to the angular frequency \\( \\omega = 55 \\text{rad/s} \\), not the peak voltage. 12V and 60V do not match the coefficient of the sine function."
    },
    "topic": [
      "AC Voltage",
      "Electric Potential",
      "Electricity & Magnetism",
      "Peak Voltage"
    ]
  },
