    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 23 @ 2021/2022",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The number of cycles the alternating current completes in one second is",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "frequency",
        "amplitude",
        "period",
        "wavelength"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "frequency"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "The number of cycles an alternating current completes in one second is defined as its frequency, which is why frequency is the correct answer. Frequency is measured in Hertz (Hz). Amplitude is the maximum value of the current, period is the time for one cycle, and wavelength applies to waves in a medium, not the definition of cycles per second."
    },
